long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1272629 xfreerdp debug output
Description of problem: After a system update the freerdp jumped from 23.20170302git210de68.fc25 to 24.20170317git8c68761.fc25 and then I'm facing the same issue as reported at https://github.com/FreeRDP/FreeRDP/issues/3518
I've downgraded the package to 12.20160909git1855e36.fc25 and is working again
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
How reproducible: It is necessary to have Windows Server 2012 R2 and RemoteApp setup
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Update or install freerdp release 23.20170302git210de68.fc25 2. Run xfreerdp /cert-ignore /app:\"||calc\" /v:server.local /u:${USER}@volt /p:${PASS}"
Actual results: Xfreerdp closes with the following error: [10:53:47:706] [2355:2356] [INFO][com.freerdp.client.common.cmdline] - loading channelEx rail [10:53:47:736] [2355:2356] [WARN][com.freerdp.core.nego] - Error: SSL_NOT_ALLOWED_BY_SERVER [10:53:47:743] [2355:2356] [WARN][com.freerdp.core.nego] - Error: SSL_NOT_ALLOWED_BY_SERVER [10:53:47:868] [2355:2356] [INFO][com.freerdp.gdi] - Local framebuffer format PIXEL_FORMAT_BGRX32 [10:53:47:869] [2355:2356] [INFO][com.freerdp.gdi] - Remote framebuffer format PIXEL_FORMAT_RGB16 [10:53:49:262] [2355:2356] [ERROR][com.freerdp.core.fastpath] - FASTPATH_UPDATETYPE_ORDERS - fastpath_recv_orders() [10:53:49:262] [2355:2356] [ERROR][com.freerdp.core.fastpath] - fastpath_recv_update() - -1 [10:53:49:262] [2355:2356] [ERROR][com.freerdp.core.fastpath] - fastpath_recv_update_data() fail [10:53:49:262] [2355:2356] [ERROR][com.freerdp.core.transport] - transport_check_fds: transport->ReceiveCallback() - -1 [10:53:49:263] [2355:2356] [ERROR][com.freerdp.core] - freerdp_check_fds() failed - 0 [10:53:49:263] [2355:2356] [INFO][com.freerdp.client.x11] - Network disconnect! [10:53:49:263] [2355:2356] [ERROR][com.freerdp.client.x11] - Failed to check FreeRDP file descriptor
Expected results: Open the remote application window
Additional info:

Can you check if it is soleved in the latest build (freerdp-2.0.0-26.20170419gitbfcf8e7)?
https://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/packageinfo?packageID=11176

(In reply to Simone Caronni from comment #1) > Can you check if it is soleved in the latest build > (freerdp-2.0.0-26.20170419gitbfcf8e7)? > > https://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/packageinfo?packageID=11176
Yes, It did solve the issue.
Thanks.
